    Product description

    Colour Name:Black  |  Style Name:Single

    Product Description

    This is a portable filing system to safely organise documents. It has a recessed handle and is stackable for easy storage. Accommodates A4 documents. Complete with 5 A4 suspension files, indexing system, lockable lid, and spare key. W370 x D220 x H295mm. Colour: Black.

    Manufacturer's Description

    Ideal home office filing system with a lockable lid.

    Box Contains

  • File Box
  • 2 Keys
  • 5 Files

    • See more

    From the manufacturer

    About Gred Products

    Established almost 20 years ago with just one product - the Home Office File Box, still manufactured in our West Midlands factory - Gred Products has assembled a constantly growing range in excess of 40 product categories. Dedicated to providing quality at extremely competitive prices, Gred sources and develops products which appeal to users in the office, at home or in education, where innovation and reliability are balanced by cost efficiency.

    Gred is consistently adding new products to its exciting ranges, and has created a number of distinctive brands, including 'Namesafe' digital safes and the 'Peel'n'Stik' notes range.

    Creating an impact

    Gred's highly visual packaging is designed for maximum impact with clear communication of product features and benefits, and can often be tailored to individual customer requirements. In a competitive market, Gred products attract attention in store.

    How are ratings calculated?
    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Yann DEPIERRE
    2.0 out of 5 stars This poor finish can be a cause of bad alignment of ...
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 28 June 2017
    Colour Name: RedStyle Name: SingleVerified Purchase
    Overall, this is a cheap solution for storing your paperwork.

    Beware though, it's made of thin metal and it is very poorly finished.
    For example, the hinges were not properly riveted, with only 1 rivet out of three on both sides, and one side have not been properly drilled. (see pictures).

    I would suggest to buy it only if you (or a friend) have the tools to properly finish it.

    This poor finish can be a cause of bad alignment of the lock.
    Also, if you force on the lid, you will bend the metal sheet it's made of. Be cautious when using it.

    DefectiveStoat
    3.0 out of 5 stars Pretty poor
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 1 October 2019
    Colour Name: RedStyle Name: SingleVerified Purchase
    I bought this after reading the reviews and thought.. how bad can it be? After all, it is cheap and it will do the job.

    Well. It does the job. But not very well. One of the tiny spot welds is broken on mine so the rear panel is a bit wobbly.

    The handle is entirely plastic and cheap. The lock is cheap like a kid’s toy- and this needs to operate to hold it closed.

    The files don’t run up and down the runners very smoothly at all and the finish is overall poor. If you dropped it on the floor I think it would probably flatten back down to sheet metal!

    Well, I’m committed now as I purchased two. They will do the job, but I’ll probably resent them every time I use them.

    One small benefit is that a4 document wallets do actually fit inside with a bit of bending to get past the rails, so I can stuff some additional things at the back.

    Try and procure something better.

    I bought a reduced price version, which is like a “second.” So was very inexpensive.     Alice
    3.0 out of 5 stars Spacious and does the job, however not the best build quality
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 18 December 2015
    Colour Name: RedStyle Name: SingleVerified Purchase
    This file is perfect for what I need it for, which is a static storage space for important documents which doesn't need to be secured. There is plenty of space and the suspension files are cheap, allowing you to put more categories in more easily.

    However, this product has both a handle and a clasp with a lock- I wouldn't trust either of them. This is mostly due to the quality of the clasp- it is extremely cheap and flimsy and I wouldn't dare lock it, in fear that I wouldn't be able to then unlock it again. I have on occasion struggled to get the clasp open as it has somehow managed to close not quite right. On the other hand, when it is closed properly, I wouldn't trust it to hold the lid closed while carrying the case by the handle.

    However, if you don't need to move it around or secure it in any way, this is an excellent option with plenty of space.
